    bindsym $mod+p exec /home/&lt;user&gt;/bin/ms-personal

Which launches urxvt with a specific -name option. For some reason, this binding does not take effect when I first launch i3; `$mod+p` has no effect. However, if I reload my i3 configuration using `$mod+shift+C`, `$mod+p` then works. Is this a known issue?</description><pubDate>Mon, 26 Nov 2012 09:09:16 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/818/some-keybindings-not-taking-effect-on-initial-i3-startup/</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Michael for &lt;p&gt;I have some custom keybindings in my .i3/config which launch specific scripts. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;bindsym $mod+p exec /home/&amp;lt;user&amp;gt;/bin/ms-personal
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which launches urxvt with a specific -name option. For some reason, this binding does not take effect when I first launch i3; &lt;code&gt;$mod+p&lt;/code&gt; has no effect. However, if I reload my i3 configuration using &lt;code&gt;$mod+shift+C&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;$mod+p&lt;/code&gt; then works. Is this a known issue?&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/818/some-keybindings-not-taking-effect-on-initial-i3-startup/?comment=819#comment-819</link><description>There is no known issue in this area, and this is not a question but a bug report. Please file it at http://bugs.i3wm.org/</description><pubDate>Mon, 26 Nov 2012 11:57:05 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/818/some-keybindings-not-taking-effect-on-initial-i3-startup/?comment=819#comment-819</guid></item></channel></rss>